post_text:
Dear Parents of Phoenix Advantage,

On Friday, March 20, 2020, Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman announced a two-week extension of school closures through Friday, April 10, 2020. Going forward, Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman will continue to provide updates and guidance about the need for continued school closures beyond that date.

Our school is still providing instruction to your students and our teachers have reached out to you regarding homework packets to be picked up. If you are unable to pick up your child‚Äôs work, please let us know and we can arrange to send it to you via U.S. Mail or a home visit. WE are here to continue to educate your students during this time, please reach out to your child‚Äôs teacher if you have any questions about their work.

We look forward to seeing all PACS students soon!

Best Regards,

Ms. Elliott, Superintendent
